==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Congo group
<hw>Con"go group</hw>. <ety>[From <er>Congo red</er>.]</ety> <def>A
group of artificial dyes with an affinity for vegetable fibers, so that
no mordant is required. Most of them are azo compounds derived from
benzidine or tolidine. Called also <altname><col><b>benzidine
dyes</b></col></altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Congolese</ent>⟦br⟧
